United States Lime & Minerals, Inc. Key Developments

United States Lime & Minerals, Inc. Reports Unaudited Consolidated Earnings and Production Results for the Second Quarter and Six Months Ended June 30, 2017
Jul 26 17
United States Lime & Minerals, Inc. reported unaudited consolidated earnings and production results for the second quarter and six months ended June 30, 2017. For the quarter, the company reported total revenues of $36,518,000 compared to $32,880,000 a year ago. Operating profit was $6,320,000 compared to $4,910,000 a year ago. Net income was $5,278,000 or $0.94 per diluted share compared to $3,687,000 or $0.66 per diluted share a year ago. 

For the six months period, the company reported total revenues of $72,671,000 compared to $66,466,000 a year ago. Operating profit was $12,138,000 compared to $10,358,000 a year ago. Net income was $9,898,000 or $1.77 per basic and diluted share compared to $7,753,000 or $1.39 per basic and diluted share a year ago.

Production volumes from the Company's natural gas interests in the second quarter 2017 totaled 142,000 MCF, sold at an average price of $3.89 per MCF, compared to 157,000 MCF, sold at an average price of $3.21 per MCF, in the comparable 2016 quarter. 

 Production volumes in the first six months 2017 from natural gas interests totaled 288,000 MCF, sold at an average price of $4.12 per MCF, compared to the first six months 2016 when 318,000 MCF was produced and sold at an average price of $2.95 per MCF.


United States Lime & Minerals, Inc. Declares Quarterly Cash Dividend, Payable September 15, 2017
Jul 26 17
United States Lime & Minerals, Inc. announced that the Board of Directors has declared a regular quarterly cash dividend of $0.135 per share on the company's common stock. This dividend is payable on September 15, 2017 to shareholders of record at the close of business on August 25, 2017.


United States Lime & Minerals, Inc. Announces Consolidated Unaudited Earnings Results for the First Quarter Ended March 31, 2017
Apr 25 17
United States Lime & Minerals, Inc. announced consolidated unaudited earnings results for the first quarter ended March 31, 2017. For the quarter, the company reported total revenues of $36,153,000 compared with $33,586,000 for the same period a year ago. Operating profit was $5,818,000 compared with $5,448,000 for the same period a year ago. Net income was $4,620,000 or $0.83 per basic and diluted share compared with $4,066,000 or $0.73 per basic and diluted share for the same period a year ago. The increase in lime and limestone revenues in the first quarter 2017, as compared to the first quarter 2016, resulted primarily from increased sales volumes of the company's lime and limestone products due to increased demand, principally from its oil and gas services customers.


